Subject: Using Your Geek for Good Instead of Evil
Description: You're the leetest of leet.  You dream in code.  Instead of helping prolong the problems of corporations for fun and money or creating state sponsored malware, what kind of good can you do with your skills?  Why bother?  Come listen to some people who are changing the world by sharing their technical abilities with others.    Speakers include:Nancy Bright, Erika Carlson, Emily Gonyer, Ken Grundberg, Albert Manero, Jen Owen, Ivan Owen - Track: Life  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Contributing to OSS - Navigating Community
Description: Hacking Open Source Software is the entire point of its existence.  Change what you don't like, fix what doesn't work for you, and enjoy.  But what about getting your patches accepted by the project? wrowe@apache.org and other participants invite you to this discussion on navigating communities, finding acceptance for your contributions, and becoming part of the bigger communities of Open Source Projects.  Speakers include:William A. Rowe Jr., Emily Gonyer - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
